{"lemma":"عَجَلَةٍ","slug":"عَجَلَةٍ","root":"ع.ج.ل","root_slug":"ع-ج-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ج-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28193","n28201","n28202","n28203"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَجِلَ (ʕajila) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"haste, hurry, speed, speediness, celerity","examples":[{"text":"أَنَا عَلَى عَجَلَةٍ.","english":"I'm in a hurry"},{"text":"فِي ٱلتَّأَنِّي ٱلسَّلَامَةُ، وَفِي ٱلْعَجَلَةِ ٱلنَّدَامَةُ.","english":"Sedateness brings welfare, hurry brings regret."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wheel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"precipitation, precipitance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of عِجْل (ʕijl, “calf”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"female calf; heifer (rare, for female calves are also called عِجْل)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Halopyrum mucronatum"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of عَجِل (ʕajil)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"At least for the abstract senses, verbal noun of عَجِلَ (ʕajila, “to hurry”).\nCompare also Hebrew עגלה (agalá, “carriage, cart”) and Hebrew מַעְגָּל (ma'agál, “circle”)\n\nFrom عِجْل (ʕijl) + ـَة (-a)."},"ipa":["/ʕa.d͡ʒa.la/","/ʕi.d͡ʒa.la/","/ʕa.d͡ʒi.la/"]}